# How to Deploy Harmonia on GitHub + Render
## Step-by-Step Beginner Guide

---

## Part 1: Create a GitHub Account & Repository

### Step 1: Sign Up for GitHub
1. Go to **github.com**
2. Click **"Sign Up"** (top right)
3. Enter your email, create a password, choose a username
4. Verify your email address
5. You're in!

### Step 2: Install Git on Your Computer

**Windows:**
1. Go to **git-scm.com/download/win**
2. Download and run the installer
3. Click "Next" through all options (defaults are fine)
4. Open **Git Bash** from Start Menu to verify: type `git --version`

**Mac:**
1. Open **Terminal** (search in Spotlight)
2. Type: `git --version`
3. If not installed, it will prompt you to install Xcode tools — click "Install"

### Step 3: Create a New Repository
1. Go to **github.com** and click the **"+"** icon (top right) → **"New repository"**
2. Fill in:
   - **Repository name:** `harmonia-website`
   - **Description:** `Harmonia - The Compatibility Engine website`
   - **Visibility:** Choose **Public** or **Private**
   - ✅ Check **"Add a README file"** — NO (we already have one)
3. Click **"Create repository"**
4. You'll see setup instructions — keep this page open

### Step 4: Upload Your Code

**Option A: Using GitHub Web (Easiest)**
1. On your new repo page, click **"uploading an existing file"**
2. Drag and drop ALL files from the unzipped `harmonia` folder
3. Scroll down, add commit message: "Initial upload"
4. Click **"Commit changes"**

**Option B: Using Git Command Line**
1. Open Terminal/Git Bash
2. Navigate to your unzipped project folder:
   ```bash
   cd path/to/harmonia
   ```
3. Initialize and push:
   ```bash
   git init
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial commit - Harmonia website"
   git branch -M main
   git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/harmonia-website.git
   git push -u origin main
   ```
4. Enter your GitHub username and password (or token) when prompted

**Note on Tokens:** GitHub now requires a Personal Access Token instead of password.
1. Go to **github.com** → Settings → Developer Settings → Personal Access Tokens → Tokens (classic)
2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
3. Give it a name, select "repo" scope, click "Generate"
4. Copy the token and use it as your password when pushing

---

## Part 2: Deploy on Render

### Step 1: Sign Up for Render
1. Go to **render.com**
2. Click **"Get Started for Free"**
3. Sign up with your **GitHub account** (recommended — links automatically)

### Step 2: Create a New Web Service
1. From the Render dashboard, click **"New +"** → **"Web Service"**
2. Under **"Build and deploy from a Git repository"**, click **"Next"**
3. Connect your GitHub account if not already connected
4. Find and select **`harmonia-website`** from the repo list
5. Click **"Connect"**

### Step 3: Configure the Service
Fill in these settings:

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| **Name** | `harmonia-website` |
| **Region** | Choose closest to you (e.g., Frankfurt for EU) |
| **Branch** | `main` |
| **Runtime** | `Node` |
| **Build Command** | `npm install` |
| **Start Command** | `npm start` |
| **Instance Type** | `Free` |

### Step 4: Deploy!
1. Click **"Create Web Service"**
2. Render will:
   - Clone your repository
   - Run `npm install` (installs Express)
   - Run `npm start` (starts the server)
3. Wait 2-3 minutes for the build to complete
4. Your site will be live at: **`https://harmonia-website.onrender.com`**

### Step 5: Verify It Works
1. Click the URL that Render provides
2. Check that:
   - ✅ Home page loads with the Celtic Knot logo
   - ✅ Navigation links work between pages
   - ✅ Dark/light theme toggle works
   - ✅ WebGL particles are visible in the background
   - ✅ P2P page shows the interactive preview
   - ✅ Mobile hamburger menu works

---

## Part 3: Updating Your Site

### Making Changes
1. Edit files in your local project folder
2. Open Terminal/Git Bash in the project folder:
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "Description of what you changed"
   git push
   ```
3. Render automatically detects the push and redeploys (takes ~2 minutes)

### Using Claude/AI to Make Changes
1. Download your project as zip from GitHub (Code → Download ZIP)
2. Upload to Claude, request changes
3. Download the updated zip from Claude
4. Extract and replace your local files
5. Push to GitHub:
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "Updated via Claude AI"
   git push
   ```

---

## Part 4: Custom Domain (Optional)

### Step 1: Buy a Domain
- **Namecheap** (namecheap.com) — affordable
- **Google Domains** → now Squarespace Domains
- **Cloudflare** (cloudflare.com) — cheapest at-cost pricing

### Step 2: Connect to Render
1. In Render dashboard → Your service → **"Settings"**
2. Scroll to **"Custom Domains"**
3. Click **"Add Custom Domain"**
4. Enter your domain (e.g., `harmonia.io`)
5. Render will give you a **CNAME record** to add to your domain DNS
6. Add the CNAME in your domain registrar's DNS settings
7. Wait 5-30 minutes for DNS propagation
8. Render automatically provisions an SSL certificate

---

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Solution |
|---------|----------|
| Build fails | Check the Render logs — usually a missing dependency. Make sure `package.json` has `express` |
| Page not found | Make sure all HTML files are in the root directory, not in a subfolder |
| CSS/JS not loading | Check file paths in HTML — should be `css/style.css` not `/css/style.css` |
| Git push rejected | Pull first: `git pull origin main --rebase` then push again |
| Site shows old version | Check Render dashboard — redeploy might still be in progress |
| Free tier sleeps | Render Free tier sleeps after 15min of inactivity. First visit takes ~30s to wake up |

---

## File Compatibility Checklist

Before deploying, verify:
- [x] `package.json` exists in root with `express` dependency
- [x] `server.js` exists in root
- [x] All HTML files reference `css/style.css` (not absolute paths)
- [x] All HTML files reference `js/app.js` and `js/webgl.js`
- [x] `assets/logo.png` exists
- [x] No file paths start with `/` (use relative paths)
- [x] `node_modules/` is NOT committed (add to `.gitignore`)

### Create .gitignore
Create a file called `.gitignore` in your project root:
```
node_modules/
.DS_Store
*.log
```
